The Naira at the official rate depreciated 0.02 per cent to exchange N307.00 against the Dollar on Tuesday.
At the Investors and Exporters (I&E) foreign exchange window also weakened 0.01 per cent to $/N362.61, having opened at N362.29, traded high at N363.00.
Investors exchanged a total of $106.83 million through the I&E window.
The local currency remained unchanged at N306.95/$ (spot) and N358.51/$ (SMIS) at the Interbank.
At the parallel market segment, the cash and transfer rates both remained unchanged to close N358.00/$ and N362.50/$ respectively.